Iran's players have been warned by their football association they could face punishment if they take selfies with female fans at the Asian Cup.

The head of the Iranian Football Federation moral committee Ali Akbar Mohammadzadeh issued the warning last week as photographs of players with women were uploaded to social media.

Female supporters are banned from attending men's sports events in the Islamic republic but not in Australia, where Iran are playing in the Asian Cup.

