Mohamedzade, quoted by Iran's Shahrvand newspaper, said: 'National team players should be aware that they won't be used as a political tool so that those who take pictures with them don't use these photos against the players.

'So according to this they should not take photos with everyone. If the players don't respect this, we will be obliged to take action.'

There have not been any details on what the punishment would be, and the IFF were contacted by Sportsmail for comment. 

